Canonical Principle

“Do not give the answer. Give the next hold.”

And the deeper version:

“A good teacher is not a ladder. A good teacher is a rock wall that teaches while it is being climbed.”

That’s a useful complement to your XP-farming idea because it formalizes how XP is acquired: not by dumping knowledge, but by creating a sequence of reachable challenges that continuously convert experience into capability.